#
# ClickIndicator: a child-process full-screen transparent overlay that paints
# a brief red dot with crosshair at each pointer position injected during
# phase 4 of kwin_restore.py.
#
# Architecture
# ────────────
# A single persistent QWidget covers the full virtual desktop (all monitors
# combined).  Its background is fully transparent; only the dots are visible.
# Each dot is a 48 px red filled circle with a white crosshair, painted at the
# requested position and erased after DOT_DURATION_MS by a QTimer.
#
# After the overlay is shown, a KWin JS script (injected via pydbus, matching
# by PID) sets keepAbove=true, onAllDesktops=true, and skipTaskbar=true so the
# overlay stays on top of all windows, is visible on every virtual desktop, and
# does not appear in the taskbar.
#
# Usage
# ─────
#   indicator = ClickIndicator()
#   indicator.start()            # spawn child, block until ready
#   indicator.show_click(x, y)   # non-blocking
#   indicator.stop()             # send sentinel, wait for child exit
